00:44:22.935 --> 00:44:24.340
Hi.

00:44:24.340 --> 00:44:25.775
I was actually
curious about what

00:44:25.775 --> 00:44:29.780
you found when you were
researching about meditation.

00:44:29.780 --> 00:44:32.660
Because I actually, I'm like
a natural born cynic generally

00:44:32.660 --> 00:44:34.370
when it comes to
things like this.

00:44:34.370 --> 00:44:37.580
But I went to a talk here
actually last month--

00:44:37.580 --> 00:44:40.340
this guy named Daniel Gorman.

00:44:40.340 --> 00:44:43.190
And it was really interesting
and actually skewed me

00:44:43.190 --> 00:44:45.650
towards--

00:44:45.650 --> 00:44:47.390
he came with a neuroscientist.

00:44:47.390 --> 00:44:49.340
And they basically
had done research

00:44:49.340 --> 00:44:53.460
where meditation and this
practice of mindfulness--

00:44:53.460 --> 00:44:57.440
there was data done where they
looked at the brains of monks

00:44:57.440 --> 00:45:01.710
and it showed that it
actually decreased stress

00:45:01.710 --> 00:45:03.070
and there was just--

00:45:03.070 --> 00:45:04.190
SPEAKER: And that's
